if you need to have 1-miner per GPU, where each miner has 1 GPU allocated, then yes, you need different hotkeys per miner.
Now, though we support DDP, whereby 1miner can train on multi-gpu setup. in that case, make sure you pass these arguments in the miner

```
--nnodes=1 # leave this to 1
--nproc_per_node=<amount of gpus>
```
everything else should work as it is

similar answer to you @JackZWeb3 

have these arguments. the `--device` argument is not needed in DDP, as it's seeing the ENV variable `CUDA_VISIBLE_DEVICES` which if you leave it blank, it'll use all the available ones, or you can be explicit `CUDA_VISIBLE_DEVICES=0,1,2,3`

```
--nnodes=1 # leave this to 1
--nproc_per_node=<amount of gpus>
```
